-- Home Depot buys back shares
-- 
-- Mon Sep 10, 2007 9:17am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/10/us-homedepot-shares-idUSN1023562720070910

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Home improvement retailer Home Depot Inc said on Monday that under a tender offer that expired on August 31, it agreed to buy 289.331 million shares of its common stock for a total value of $10.7 billion. 

 Following the buyback, the company said it now expects fiscal 2007 earnings per share from continuing operations to decline between 7 and 9 percent. Previously, Home Depot had said it expected 2007 earnings per share to decrease between 12 and 15 percent. (See  here  -- Reuters' retail and consumer blog) (Reporting by  Aarthi Sivaraman )